WEBVTT

00:00:00.719 --> 00:00:07.520
Yeah. Um, I'm so proud of how I've done

00:00:04.160 --> 00:00:09.360
this Olympics. I joke, I'm not a betting

00:00:07.520 --> 00:00:11.840
woman, but if I were, I took a big

00:00:09.360 --> 00:00:13.360
gamble this time because I chose to do

00:00:11.840 --> 00:00:15.280
three events knowing that I hadn't

00:00:13.360 --> 00:00:17.199
trained halfpipe in two months, knowing

00:00:15.280 --> 00:00:18.640
that I would miss the halfpipe training

00:00:17.199 --> 00:00:20.080
because of in case I made big air

00:00:18.640 --> 00:00:23.039
finals, which I also hadn't competed in

00:00:20.080 --> 00:00:25.840
in four years, mind you. And so being

00:00:23.039 --> 00:00:27.920
able to really trust myself that when it

00:00:25.840 --> 00:00:29.760
came down to the moment, I would be able

00:00:27.920 --> 00:00:32.320
to perform to the best of my ability

00:00:29.760 --> 00:00:35.040
regardless of metal color or metal in

00:00:32.320 --> 00:00:36.880
general. Um, but that's a big bet. And

00:00:35.040 --> 00:00:38.640
also just the difficulty of competing in

00:00:36.880 --> 00:00:41.120
three events, making finals in three

00:00:38.640 --> 00:00:43.600
events. I had to compete six times. And

00:00:41.120 --> 00:00:46.000
I kind of liken it to a marathon, but

00:00:43.600 --> 00:00:47.520
the pace of a 100 meter dash because

00:00:46.000 --> 00:00:49.920
every day is the Olympics. I have to

00:00:47.520 --> 00:00:51.360
give 100% every day. So there's no day

00:00:49.920 --> 00:00:53.440
that I can just chill a little because

00:00:51.360 --> 00:00:55.600
every day matters. So I guess what I

00:00:53.440 --> 00:00:58.960
mean to say with that is I have done

00:00:55.600 --> 00:01:00.960
something that I I took a big risk in

00:00:58.960 --> 00:01:03.760
trusting myself and I'm glad that I did.

00:01:00.960 --> 00:01:06.080
Um I walk away as the most decorated

00:01:03.760 --> 00:01:07.760
free skier of all time, male or female.

00:01:06.080 --> 00:01:11.040
I have the most gold medals of any free

00:01:07.760 --> 00:01:13.280
skier ever, male or female. And that is

00:01:11.040 --> 00:01:15.840
something that I'm so so proud of. Is

00:01:13.280 --> 00:01:17.439
unbelievable to me is still surreal. Um,

00:01:15.840 --> 00:01:21.119
and so I appreciate all the people who

00:01:17.439 --> 00:01:23.360
support me and who hopefully take up

00:01:21.119 --> 00:01:24.880
free skiing maybe because of me. Um, or

00:01:23.360 --> 00:01:27.040
at least maybe heard about free skiing

00:01:24.880 --> 00:01:29.520
for the first time. That those are the

00:01:27.040 --> 00:01:31.119
people who I do it for. Otherwise, I

00:01:29.520 --> 00:01:32.880
just encourage people to use that energy

00:01:31.119 --> 00:01:34.479
and direct it to something um that makes

00:01:32.880 --> 00:01:36.079
the world better in their own way. I

00:01:34.479 --> 00:01:39.200
think I'm making the most amount of good

00:01:36.079 --> 00:01:42.000
with the powers that I have as um a

00:01:39.200 --> 00:01:44.000
22-year-old athlete. And I think in this

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:45.600
way I'm benefiting the most people. If

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:46.960
people disagree with me, if they have

00:01:45.600 --> 00:01:48.880
other skill sets, which I'm sure they

00:01:46.960 --> 00:01:50.479
do, then I encourage them to direct that

00:01:48.880 --> 00:01:54.240
direct it elsewhere and to make the

00:01:50.479 --> 00:01:58.799
world better in their own way.

00:01:54.240 --> 00:02:02.240
As young women, I think it is easy to

00:01:58.799 --> 00:02:04.479
doubt. Um, and I mean this as in like

00:02:02.240 --> 00:02:08.720
instilled, you know, selfinstilled

00:02:04.479 --> 00:02:10.640
self-doubt, but also maybe external

00:02:08.720 --> 00:02:12.319
subtleties and like little micro things

00:02:10.640 --> 00:02:14.160
that make you doubt yourself and over

00:02:12.319 --> 00:02:15.760
time make you afraid to try. That's why

00:02:14.160 --> 00:02:17.440
we see rates of young women

00:02:15.760 --> 00:02:19.360
participating in sports drop off

00:02:17.440 --> 00:02:23.040
precipitously between the ages of 11 and

00:02:19.360 --> 00:02:25.680
14. And so, as far as trusting yourself,

00:02:23.040 --> 00:02:29.200
the power of sport is unparalleled

00:02:25.680 --> 00:02:31.840
because it is evidence over affirmation.

00:02:29.200 --> 00:02:34.160
It's you don't tell yourself, "Oh, I can

00:02:31.840 --> 00:02:36.879
handle the pressure. Oh, I'm so great."

00:02:34.160 --> 00:02:38.160
You do it time and again. And another

00:02:36.879 --> 00:02:40.000
thing, you know, I said this earlier in

00:02:38.160 --> 00:02:41.440
an interview. I said, "Sports are really

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:43.680
honest because you can't lie to

00:02:41.440 --> 00:02:45.519
yourself. You know when you stayed late

00:02:43.680 --> 00:02:47.120
and other people weren't there. You

00:02:45.519 --> 00:02:48.720
know, when you showed up early and other

00:02:47.120 --> 00:02:51.599
people weren't there, you know, when you

00:02:48.720 --> 00:02:54.000
gave 100% in training day in day out for

00:02:51.599 --> 00:02:55.840
months, for months." And so it's not

00:02:54.000 --> 00:02:57.760
about, you know, at the last second I

00:02:55.840 --> 00:02:59.760
tell myself a chipper little line and

00:02:57.760 --> 00:03:01.840
call it a day. It's the fact that I look

00:02:59.760 --> 00:03:04.720
back on quite literally years, like

00:03:01.840 --> 00:03:06.959
decade of hard work of pouring my heart

00:03:04.720 --> 00:03:08.560
and soul into this sport. And so it's,

00:03:06.959 --> 00:03:10.720
yeah, it's trusting myself, but it's

00:03:08.560 --> 00:03:12.319
building that trust every day. Um, and

00:03:10.720 --> 00:03:13.760
so that's a big reason why I encourage

00:03:12.319 --> 00:03:15.920
more young girls to get into sports

00:03:13.760 --> 00:03:17.680
because I think that the power it has to

00:03:15.920 --> 00:03:20.480
build and instill that confidence in

00:03:17.680 --> 00:03:21.920
people um is is a really special and and

00:03:20.480 --> 00:03:23.040
unique form.

00:03:21.920 --> 00:03:25.920
>> Oh, yeah. Yeah, I guess I didn't answer

00:03:23.040 --> 00:03:28.480
the second question. So, um, it's

00:03:25.920 --> 00:03:31.440
fashion week in Milan, so I have the

00:03:28.480 --> 00:03:32.959
other job, the other fashion thing. Um,

00:03:31.440 --> 00:03:35.760
no, no, I'm really excited to just

00:03:32.959 --> 00:03:37.599
explore some other avenues, be creative,

00:03:35.760 --> 00:03:38.959
and explore my femininity through

00:03:37.599 --> 00:03:40.879
fashion, which is something I've always

00:03:38.959 --> 00:03:43.920
loved, and to kind of put that in

00:03:40.879 --> 00:03:45.120
juxtaposition with skiing and and with

00:03:43.920 --> 00:03:47.440
sports. And I think that they can

00:03:45.120 --> 00:03:49.519
coexist so beautifully. And so, I hope

00:03:47.440 --> 00:03:52.480
to represent that um, next week in

00:03:49.519 --> 00:03:54.720
Milan.

00:03:52.480 --> 00:03:57.840
A big thing is I'm not afraid to try. I

00:03:54.720 --> 00:04:00.319
take big risks and for the last two

00:03:57.840 --> 00:04:03.200
Olympics it's worked out. Um but even if

00:04:00.319 --> 00:04:05.519
it hadn't, I think I left nothing on the

00:04:03.200 --> 00:04:07.040
table. Like I know that looking back at

00:04:05.519 --> 00:04:09.360
this Olympics and the months that

00:04:07.040 --> 00:04:11.120
preceded it, there is quite literally

00:04:09.360 --> 00:04:14.319
nothing that I could have done more.

00:04:11.120 --> 00:04:16.000
Like I did everything I could um every

00:04:14.319 --> 00:04:18.160
single day. Every single thing that I

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:20.079
could like if you can think of something

00:04:18.160 --> 00:04:21.919
like oh I should do this now. I've done

00:04:20.079 --> 00:04:23.440
it. I have done every single thing I

00:04:21.919 --> 00:04:25.199
could possibly do for this Olympics. And

00:04:23.440 --> 00:04:27.440
so it's like if things didn't go my way,

00:04:25.199 --> 00:04:29.440
I wouldn't regret feeling unprepared. I

00:04:27.440 --> 00:04:31.360
wouldn't regret feeling like I could

00:04:29.440 --> 00:04:32.800
have done more. And so that I also think

00:04:31.360 --> 00:04:34.880
instills a bit of confidence in you

00:04:32.800 --> 00:04:36.080
because you can never control the

00:04:34.880 --> 00:04:37.600
result. You can never control the

00:04:36.080 --> 00:04:38.960
outcome, but you can control the

00:04:37.600 --> 00:04:42.759
preparation. And most importantly, you

00:04:38.960 --> 00:04:42.759
can fall in love with the process.

00:04:45.440 --> 00:04:48.440
Fore!

00:05:04.080 --> 00:05:07.080
Foreign! Foreign!

00:05:20.400 --> 00:05:23.400
Um,

00:05:39.039 --> 00:05:44.639
thank you, Charlotte. That's very kind.

00:05:41.199 --> 00:05:47.360
Um, oh, man.

00:05:44.639 --> 00:05:49.360
Do I think I think overall I'm just a

00:05:47.360 --> 00:05:51.520
pensive person. Like I'm a very

00:05:49.360 --> 00:05:53.199
introspective I'm an introspective young

00:05:51.520 --> 00:05:55.360
woman. Like I spend a lot of time in my

00:05:53.199 --> 00:05:58.000
head. Um and it's not a bad place to be.

00:05:55.360 --> 00:05:59.919
I I journal a lot. I break down all of

00:05:58.000 --> 00:06:02.800
my thought processes. I think I apply a

00:05:59.919 --> 00:06:05.440
very analytical lens to my own thinking.

00:06:02.800 --> 00:06:06.720
And I kind of modify it because it's so

00:06:05.440 --> 00:06:08.560
interesting. You can control what you

00:06:06.720 --> 00:06:10.160
think. Like you can control how you

00:06:08.560 --> 00:06:11.919
think and therefore you can control who

00:06:10.160 --> 00:06:13.520
you are. And especially as a young

00:06:11.919 --> 00:06:15.280
person like I'm 22 so with

00:06:13.520 --> 00:06:16.720
neuroplasticity on my side, I can

00:06:15.280 --> 00:06:18.000
literally become exactly who I want to

00:06:16.720 --> 00:06:20.240
be. How cool is that? Like how

00:06:18.000 --> 00:06:22.960
empowering is that, right? And so the

00:06:20.240 --> 00:06:25.360
fact is I get to become every day the

00:06:22.960 --> 00:06:27.360
kind of person that me at age eight

00:06:25.360 --> 00:06:28.720
would revere. Like I would be obsessed

00:06:27.360 --> 00:06:30.240
with me today. Are you kidding? I would

00:06:28.720 --> 00:06:32.080
love me. And I think that's the biggest

00:06:30.240 --> 00:06:34.080
flex of all time that you can have like

00:06:32.080 --> 00:06:36.080
little younger you be proud of you

00:06:34.080 --> 00:06:37.360
today. And so I guess for me it's like I

00:06:36.080 --> 00:06:39.039
yes I spend a lot of time in my own

00:06:37.360 --> 00:06:41.120
head. Yes, I think a lot. But it's not

00:06:39.039 --> 00:06:43.280
really like in an egotistical kind of

00:06:41.120 --> 00:06:44.800
way. It's in like a tinkering like a

00:06:43.280 --> 00:06:45.919
scientist kind of way. I'm always like

00:06:44.800 --> 00:06:47.840
trying to modify. I'm trying to think

00:06:45.919 --> 00:06:49.840
how can I be better? How can I approach

00:06:47.840 --> 00:06:52.160
my own brain the way that I approach my

00:06:49.840 --> 00:06:55.280
craft of free skiing um so that I can be

00:06:52.160 --> 00:06:58.800
better tomorrow than I was today?

00:06:55.280 --> 00:07:01.360
>> Yeah, I think for me

00:06:58.800 --> 00:07:03.599
global beneficial impact is like my

00:07:01.360 --> 00:07:05.440
central theme. Um and there are a lot of

00:07:03.599 --> 00:07:06.639
different avenues that anybody can do

00:07:05.440 --> 00:07:08.800
that and I think it's more assessing

00:07:06.639 --> 00:07:12.080
your individual skill set and trying to

00:07:08.800 --> 00:07:13.759
say okay what is the way that I can as a

00:07:12.080 --> 00:07:16.639
person do the most good in the world.

00:07:13.759 --> 00:07:19.520
Um, so right now I'm young, I'm

00:07:16.639 --> 00:07:22.479
energetic, my body is like physically as

00:07:19.520 --> 00:07:23.680
capable as it can be compared to, you

00:07:22.479 --> 00:07:24.800
know, 30 years down the line. So it

00:07:23.680 --> 00:07:26.080
makes the most sense for me to do that

00:07:24.800 --> 00:07:28.880
through the avenues that I'm exploring

00:07:26.080 --> 00:07:30.080
now, fashion, sport, and skiing. Um,

00:07:28.880 --> 00:07:31.919
down the line, I think it will

00:07:30.080 --> 00:07:35.360
absolutely take a different form. Yeah,

00:07:31.919 --> 00:07:38.080
I think as I age and as I grow and um,

00:07:35.360 --> 00:07:40.080
the like I guess avenue of like highest

00:07:38.080 --> 00:07:41.919
optimization will change. I'm not going

00:07:40.080 --> 00:07:44.160
to be too specific in answering that

00:07:41.919 --> 00:07:45.680
because I don't want to commit myself to

00:07:44.160 --> 00:07:47.440
something. But do I have ideas? Yes,

00:07:45.680 --> 00:07:49.360
absolutely.

00:07:47.440 --> 00:07:51.840
So, when I was when I had this press

00:07:49.360 --> 00:07:54.080
conference four years ago, a lot of it

00:07:51.840 --> 00:07:56.879
was theoretical. You know, I say I want

00:07:54.080 --> 00:07:58.080
to inspire more girls to try skiing. I

00:07:56.879 --> 00:07:59.360
don't even need to do that anymore

00:07:58.080 --> 00:08:02.479
because now I can just look at the

00:07:59.360 --> 00:08:04.000
numbers. 350 million people tried snow

00:08:02.479 --> 00:08:06.720
sports for the first time. there's

00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:09.199
double-digit increase growth in the

00:08:06.720 --> 00:08:13.360
industry both in terms of snowport

00:08:09.199 --> 00:08:16.720
impressions in terms of um sponsorships,

00:08:13.360 --> 00:08:18.879
money in the sport. This is huge because

00:08:16.720 --> 00:08:20.319
it's not just about okay, it is about

00:08:18.879 --> 00:08:22.080
there's people in China, there are kids

00:08:20.319 --> 00:08:24.000
in China, there are girls in China whose

00:08:22.080 --> 00:08:25.599
lives are going to be touched by the

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:28.960
beautiful and wonderful power of sport.

00:08:25.599 --> 00:08:32.000
So that in and of itself is absolutely

00:08:28.960 --> 00:08:33.839
measured impact that I think I had

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:35.760
always wanted. I reached that goal and I

00:08:33.839 --> 00:08:37.599
exceeded it. Um the second thing is

00:08:35.760 --> 00:08:40.080
within the industry itself, the ski

00:08:37.599 --> 00:08:41.839
industry, there are more eyes on this

00:08:40.080 --> 00:08:43.120
sport than there were four years ago.

00:08:41.839 --> 00:08:46.399
There are more people paying attention

00:08:43.120 --> 00:08:48.320
to it now. Um the fact is a rising tide

00:08:46.399 --> 00:08:50.560
raises all boats. And so this is also

00:08:48.320 --> 00:08:51.760
good for every other athlete competing

00:08:50.560 --> 00:08:55.279
regardless of what country you compete

00:08:51.760 --> 00:08:56.959
for. And so that kind of mentality of I

00:08:55.279 --> 00:08:59.519
want to bring the sport to more people

00:08:56.959 --> 00:09:02.000
to hopefully benefit people outside the

00:08:59.519 --> 00:09:04.399
